{{!
    @template mod_fastpix/view

    Renders the FastPix player state (ready). The player wrapper + coverage
    bar live in the mod_fastpix/player_wrapper partial so they can also be
    rendered client-side by processing_state_poller for the in-place
    processing→player swap (no full-page reload).

    The player AMD module's init() is triggered from view.php via
    js_call_amd (NOT from an inline-JS block here) because the canonical mount
    payload is built server-side by view_state_player::to_player_payload().

    NOTE — never write a curly-brace pair inside this comment. Mustache treats
    the first closing brace pair it finds as the comment terminator, so such a
    token leaks the rest of the comment as visible text on the page.

    Context variables: see mod_fastpix/player_wrapper.

    Example context (json):
    {}
